The paper deals with image inpainting using generative adversarial networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method also incorporates high-level semantics in the context, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a joint loss function and novel measures for evaluation indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The preservation of spatial structures suggests a possible connection to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of image inpainting as a specific application suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
